s="text-gray-600">Precision Medicine Startup, Greece</p></div></div></div><div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 shadow-lg"><div class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full"><p class="text-gray-700 italic mb-4">&quot;<!-- -->I have been using the continuous care platform for several months and it has made a big impact in my practice, allowing me to monitor my patients more efficiently.<!-- -->&quot;</p><div><p class="text-gray-700 font-medium">Dr. Marie Christina Felix Douyon</p><p class="text-gray-600">Pulmonologist, Haiti</p></div></div></div></div></div></section><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the Provider Mobile App in the Virtual Practice?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Provider Mobile App is the iOS and Android companion to the Virtual Practice platform. It allows doctors and healthcare providers to manage consultations, capture AI-powered notes, review patient charts, and communicate securely with patients while on the go."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does the Provider App include full practice administration?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. Full configuration and administration features are available in the Virtual Practice Manager (web interface). The Provider App focuses on what providers need most: consultations, patient management, records access, secure messaging, and AI-powered documentation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I use AI Scribe from the mobile app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The Provider App includes the AI Scribe feature so you can dictate encounters or capture ambient conversations and have them converted into structured consultation notes, directly from your phone or tablet."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What types of consultations can providers manage in the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The app supports multiple consultation types:\n\nVideo visits for telehealth\n\nText consults for asynchronous communication\n\nIn-person visit support for documenting office encounters\n\nRemote monitoring for reviewing patient-generated health data and alerts"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is the Provider App more secure than texting patients directly?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Unlike SMS, WhatsApp, or personal calls, the Provider App uses encrypted, HIPAA-appropriate messaging that keeps PHI safe, protects your personal phone number, and creates an auditable record of patient communications."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can providers get compensated for out-of-clinic communication using the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, where regulations and payer policies allow, the Provider App makes it easier to document, track, and bill for out-of-clinic communications such as asynchronous e-visits. The app time-stamps and records these interactions in the patient's health record."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does the app replace my desktop or web EHR?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. The Provider App is designed as a mobile companion to the Virtual Practice web platform. It brings key clinical features to your phone but does not replace the full web dashboard for administrative and configuration tasks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the Provider App free or do I need to pay extra?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Every Virtual Practice account includes the free Virtual Practice Provider App (iOS and Android). For organizations that want their own branded version, a white-labelled Provider App is available as a paid add-on."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What kinds of providers use the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The app is designed for solo practitioners, small clinics, and healthcare startups alike. It scales from individual use cases to team-based practices that need secure mobile access to consultations and records."}},{"@type":"Question","nam